Ambassador Cathy Russell has been appointed as the next Executive Director of UNICEF by the UN Secretary-General. She has been a trusted advisor to Jill and Joe Biden for nearly 30 years and has shown leadership, experience, wisdom, and empathy. Russell has worked tirelessly to advocate for children and empower women and girls, previously serving as the United States Ambassador for Global Women's Issues in the Obama-Biden Administration. Under her leadership, the White House Office of Presidential Personnel has broken records in hiring speed and diversity. Gautam Raghavan, who has worked closely with Russell, will take over as the new Director of the White House Office of Presidential Personnel.